{
  "texts": [
    "For example, consider the code [[144, 12, 12]] from Extended Data Table 1.",
    "Then A = x 3 + y + y 2, A 2 = y andA 3 = y 2.",
    "Thus A A y y y = = T 3 2 2 -1that has order m = 6.",
    "The inner cycle of a wheel graph alternates between Z-check and R-data vertices.Edges of the inner cycle alternate between those generated by A T 3(as one moves from a check to a data vertex) and A 2 (as one moves from a data to a check vertex).",
    "The length of the inner cycle is equal to the order of the matrix A A T 3 2 that is the transpose of A A T 3 2 considered earlier."
  ]
}